I am assistant professor (_Maître de conférences_) at the [university of Lille 1][ustl] ([UFR IEEA][ieea]) since september 2008.

I [teach](teaching/index.html) programming and software engineering at [Telecom Lille 1][telecom],
and [research](./research.html) on reengineering at [Inria][] within the [RMoD project-team][rmod].

I'm a co-author of the open-source books [Squeak by Example][sbe] and [Pharo by Example][pbe].

##### Curriculum
I received an engineering degree in computer science from [Insa][] in 2001, and obtained my Ph.D in 2005 from the [university of Rennes 1][rennes1], France ([details here](curriculum.html)).

